<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-16T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3437: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-16T12:00:00-03:00">December 16,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 16—11:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>60. Confidential for the President and Phillips. I find that resolution
                            to end Chaco war proposes that we agree to sanctions. I have taken steps
                            designed to keep the United States Government out of this
                            obligation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>